<heading bold="true" box="[151,1021,1967,1994]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,1021,1967,1994]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">
1. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,417,1967,1994]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">
<taxonomicName authority="Chujo, 1973" authorityName="Chujo" authorityYear="1973" box="[181,293,1967,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Melalgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">Melalgus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Chujo, 1973" authorityName="Chujo" authorityYear="1973" box="[300,577,1967,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Melalgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
japonicus 
<bibRefCitation author="Chujo, M." box="[425,577,1967,1994]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" pagination="10" refId="ref2481" refString="Chujo, M. (1973) An unknown Bostrichidae collected from Tsushima, Japan. Tokai-shibuho, Japan Entomological Society, 26, 10. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1973">Chûjô, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lesne, 1902)" baseAuthorityName="Lesne" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[639,1021,1967,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Melalgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batillus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[639,848,1967,1994]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">Melalgus batillus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lesne, P." box="[863,1013,1967,1993]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" pagination="223 - 224" refId="ref2660" refString="Lesne, P. (1902) Les Bostrychides indo-chinois du genre Heterarthron (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1902, 223 - 224. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1902.23097" type="journal article" year="1902">Lesne, 1902</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="591" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1967,2030]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1437,151,537]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="591" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chujo" authorityYear="1973" box="[199,345,2004,2029]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Melalgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[199,345,2004,2029]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="590">M. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by a Japanese entomologist M. Chûjô from Tsushima Island (
<bibRefCitation author="Chujo, M." box="[1191,1324,2003,2029]" pageId="0" pageNumber="590" pagination="10" refId="ref2481" refString="Chujo, M. (1973) An unknown Bostrichidae collected from Tsushima, Japan. Tokai-shibuho, Japan Entomological Society, 26, 10. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1973">Chûjô 1973</bibRefCitation>
) based on a single male. The author provided the species description in Japanese, but the article contains two photographs of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chujo" authorityYear="1973" box="[151,296,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Melalgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[151,296,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">M. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and Latin names, including the name of the new species. As 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chujo" authorityYear="1973" box="[969,1114,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Melalgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[969,1114,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">M. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described in a magazine of local circulation, not easily available, the species was not included in the world’s catalogue of the 
<taxonomicName authority="(Borowski &amp; Wegrzynowicz 2007)" baseAuthorityName="Borowski &amp; Wegrzynowicz" baseAuthorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Bostrichidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Borowski, J. &amp; Wegrzynowicz, P." box="[159,539,259,285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" refId="ref2305" refString="Borowski, J. &amp; Wegrzynowicz, P. (2007) World Catalogue of Bostrichidae (Coleoptera). Mantis, Olsztyn, 247 pp., 8 pls." type="book" year="2007">Borowski &amp; Węgrzynowicz 2007</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. For the same reasons the species was not included in the Palaearctic catalogue, either (Borowski 2007), although Tsushima Island lies between 
<collectingCountry box="[854,917,295,321]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">Japan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[970,1112,295,321]" name="South Korea" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">South Korea</collectingCountry>
, i.e. in the Palaearctic region. In 2021 the 
<typeStatus box="[292,389,331,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chujo" authorityYear="1973" box="[431,578,331,356]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Melalgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[431,578,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">M. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found and is now held in the collection of Ehime University (EUMJ). Based on the 
<typeStatus box="[313,410,367,393]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">holotype</typeStatus>
and several other specimens (including females) the species was redescribed (
<bibRefCitation author="Yoshitomi, H." pageId="1" pageNumber="591" pagination="69 - 72" refId="ref2995" refString="Yoshitomi, H. (2021) Redescription of Melalgus japonicus Chujo (Coleoptera: Bostrichidae: Polycaoninae). Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 27 (1), 69 - 72." type="journal article" year="2021">Yoshitomi 2021</bibRefCitation>
). The author provided a detailed description of the species, colour photographs and black-and-white figures of male genital segments of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chujo" authorityYear="1973" box="[431,575,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Melalgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[431,575,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">M. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The detailed description leaves no doubt as to the fact that the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chujo" authorityYear="1973" box="[1268,1412,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Melalgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[1268,1412,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">M. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lesne, 1902)" baseAuthorityName="Lesne" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[378,658,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Melalgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batillus">
<emphasis box="[378,497,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="591">M. batillus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lesne, P." box="[511,650,475,501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="591" pagination="223 - 224" refId="ref2660" refString="Lesne, P. (1902) Les Bostrychides indo-chinois du genre Heterarthron (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1902, 223 - 224. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1902.23097" type="journal article" year="1902">Lesne, 1902</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the most common representative of a genus occurring in the Mainland Southeast Asia. Full synonymy of the species along with its geographical distribution is presented below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
